You should practice writing some methods.  Once you have at least one star on Warmups, Strings, Logics, Arrays, and AP-1, continue with the assignment.
https://codingbat.com/java

You are encouraged to return to CodingBat and try to complete every assignment you can.
On one hand, you'll learn much about return statements, parameters, and loops.  That's great.
More importantly, after you try to run a code, you'll see several examples of arguments and whether they worked.
These will really help you think of The One Exception the more you do.
For a String input, it'll always try "".  Your code should work there as well as for a normal String.
For a number input, it'll always try 0, a negative number, a decimal.  Your code should work there as well as for a normal number.
